		From mentor to brother
		You might know Kyle Negrete as a punter on USC's football team, but Joel Anderson knows him as a friend. Anderson is an artist who happens to have autism. Watch their story.
	
	
  
  
    Back to the beginning




Cash registers ringing at big-box stores and luxe boutiques
An uptick in the economy has two USC Marshall School of Business faculty members optimistic about different segments of the retail world: big-box stores like Walmart and luxury brands like TAG Heuer. The early verdict: Tiffany's little blue box might be found under a few more Christmas trees this year.
Read the full story at USC News



Apocalypse, shmapocalypse
If you put off your Christmas shopping because of the Mayan apocalypse, you might want to consider making a last-minute run to the mall. A USC anthropologist and expert on the ancient Mesoamerican people explains why the alleged prediction of doomsday shouldn't keep you up at night with worry.
Read the full story at USC News



Foshay player shoots and scores with new uniforms
No matter how good your hoops skills, it's tough to look unified as a basketball team without uniforms. Now, thanks to a student who reached out to local sporting goods companies, Foshay Learning Center has landed new jerseys, shorts and shoes. The plucky teenager is a USC Neighborhood Academic Initiative student.
Read the full story at USC News



